postcontent: This is a custom build AR15 that is designed for literally any situation--fun time on the range, tactical scenarios, and even zombie apocalypse/end of the world kinda thing. If you ever wanted to have an AR with everything you could ask for--2 magazines and weatherproof case included--this is the AR for you. I specifically built this rifle to be ready for anything. Time and consideration have gone into each and every piece and addition. I have taken the time to think of everything so you don't have to. Below is the list of parts and additions:1:8 Mid-Length 16" barrel for reduced recoil and reduced wear and tear12" Free Float M-Lok rail for increased accuracy and space for attachments (lights/lasers)BCM vertical foregrip that allows for an angled grip style1-8x24mm Vortex Strike Eagle Scope (easily transition between 8x zoom to 4x--best of both worlds)(Shockproof, waterproof, fogproof)Diamondhead style 45 degree offset flip sights (in case your optic is zoomed and targets happen to approach you at a closer distance OR if for some reason the optic goes down)Raptor style ambi charging handleAmbidextrous safety selectorMAGPUL BAD lever (makes reloads SO much faster)ODIN Works XMR 3 extended magazine release (again faster reloads)Anti-Pivot trigger pin for added reliabilityExtended Takedown pins for ease (You'll know if you've had rifles before just how difficult these can be to manipulate)MAGPUL MOE polymer trigger guard for added room (and space if you want to use glovesERGO pistol grip with beaver tail (allows for high comfortable grip = more accurate shots)Hogue Adjustable stock (so comfortable and barely and wiggle--certainly much better than standard stocks on the market)2 Gen M3 PMAGS (so durable)My most favorite part is the BCG. title: For Sale:  HK91 Clone made by AZ Expert Arms w/Mags/Spares/Accessories
postcontent: This is a Heckler and Koch 91 clone, built in 2004 by Derek Huffman of Arizona Expert Arms using an excellent parts kit on a JLD (PTR) receiver and trunnion. You can google and confirm that Derek does outstanding work. This is a beautiful rifle with HK black moly over parkerizing. Paddle mag release option installed. Currently has soft buffer installed. Round count since it was built is 100-200. The SEF trigger pack was converted to semi-auto only using the ATF friendly method of removing the front bottom portion of the trigger housing that would hold the auto-sear and welding in a bracket. The “F” marking was welded in, the “E” marking was converted to a “F”, and a selector stop added. This makes it a short throw from Safe to Fire. It did have a faux pin added (i.e., the heads of a push pin were glued to the lower to make it appear like an actual pinned lower), but one side has come off. If desired, it would be an easy fix to cut and glue a new one.Included Accessories: A3 collapsible stock; Brugger & Thomet Universal Scope Mount (overbuilt and solid); Specter gear 3-point sling, black; 17 magazines, some like new, some with wear and tear; sight adjustment screwdriver/tool; Spare parts (bolt, complete; bolt carrier; firing pin; stock pins); Polymer lower, never used, with extended safety; cheap, but functional, metal bipod for wide forearm. §922(r) ComplianceThe HK91/G3 has 17 parts under §922(r) (http://thegunwiki.com/Gunwiki/BuildG3VerifyCompliance).US Parts (7): Receiver, Trunnion, Trigger, Sear (technically a disconnect), Hammer, Pistol Grip, Cocking HandleForeign (9): Barrel, Flashhider, Bolt, Bolt Carrier, Trigger Housing, Handguard, Mag Bodies, Mag Followers, Mag FloorplatesUS or Foreign: The fixed buttstock is a US made part. The collapsing buttstock is a foreign part.***Can ship to your FFL via ShipMyGuns. Rifle will ship in a Sack-Up, inside of a plastic case, include of cardboard box. Accessories will ship separately.
